## Multi-language and Localization

The platform supports internationalization through **Japanese Translation** content and localized documentation, with plans for additional language support across the interface and documentation.

## Content Management System

The underlying content management system uses a collection-based architecture with features including:
- Multi-site support (English and Japanese)
- Content propagation controls
- Revision management
- URL routing with slug-based patterns
- Preview capabilities with live refresh
- Taxonomy support for content categorization
- Structured navigation injection
- Date-based content visibility controls

Route patterns follow consistent conventions like `/analytics/{slug}`, `/sdks/{platform}/{slug}`, `/apis/{product}/{slug}`, and `/feature-experiment/{category}/{slug}`, providing intuitive navigation and content organization.

The platform represents a comprehensive analytics ecosystem designed to support product teams throughout the entire user lifecycle, from initial data collection through advanced experimentation and user engagement optimization.